description: The man tried to attack officers in the city of Gelsenkirchen, but terrorism is not suspected.
title: Gelsenkirchen knifeman killed by German police 'mentally ill'
title_page: Gelsenkirchen knifeman killed by German police 'mentally ill' - BBC News
maintext: Police say a search of the man's flat later did not suggest a terrorist motive. The 37-year-old Turkish citizen is thought to have been mentally ill.
